<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-480] FLE should perform leader check when node is not leading and add vote of follower</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-480</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As a server may join leader election while others have already elected a leader, it is necessary that a server handles some special cases of leader election when notifications are from servers that are either LEADING or FOLLOWING. In such special cases, we check if we have received a message from the leader to declare a leader elected. This check does not consider the case that the process performing the check might be a recently elected leader, and consequently the check fails.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch also adds a new case, which corresponds to adding a vote to recvset when the notification is from a process LEADING or FOLLOWING. This fixes the case raised in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-475&quot; title=&quot;FLENewEpochTest failed on nightly builds.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ZOOKEEPER-475&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;ZOOKEEPER-475&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
